      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Can you use both the Big Five and MBTI together?</summary>
        <p>Yes, many people find value in using both models for different purposes. The Big Five provides a precise, research-backed personality profile useful for predicting life outcomes and career fit. The MBTI offers a simpler, type-based framework that works well for team-building discussions and casual self-exploration. Using the Big Five for deeper self-knowledge and the MBTI as a conversational starting point leverages the strengths of each model.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Why is the MBTI still so popular if it is less scientific?</summary>
